SP.P:
No more about conscience.—But come, I'll put it to the trial, and here is the ordeal,
(takes out a purse);
here is the general absolution that salves all consciences.—This opens and shuts the mouths of the most vociferous orators, blinds the eyes of the church, deafens the ears of magi∣strates, obliterates the judgment of the law, arrests the arm of justice, and dries up the fountains of mercy. How feels your conscience now?

Here, firrah;
(gives money.)
This can procure you every thing but that you want most, honesty.
